README for Project 1 - Chat client/server
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
chatserv.py

First we need to give it executable permissions: chmod +x chatserv.py

Run the executable ./chatserv.py <server_port> <-- this doesn't work for some reason

It can also be run by typing: python chatserv.py <server_port>  <-- this works just fine
Example: "python chatserv.py 30050"
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
chat_client.c

To Compile: gcc chat_client.c -o chatclient

To run: ./chatclient <host> <server_port>
Example: "./chatclient flip2 30050"
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Note: chat_client must send the first message.
Note: tested on flip1, flip2, and flip3
Resources: https://beej.us/guide/bgnet/ ; discussion Q&A ; https://pymotw.com/2/socket/tcp.html 